This paper deals with the problem of contextualizing a knowledge graph for a specific task, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of heuristics and algorithms to extract relevant information from the knowledge graph, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and graph databases, which are relevant to the categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
